{"number":58472,"title":"[ComputeLimit] Docs: Add service-specific examples and snippets for new GA resources","body":"## Documentation Gap

**Package:** `Azure.ResourceManager.ComputeLimit`
**Service directory:** `sdk/computelimit/Azure.ResourceManager.ComputeLimit/`
**Triggered by:** PR #57628 by `@azure-sdk` (co-authored by `@dapzhang`, `@hebin-huang`, `@ajbhal`)

## What Changed

PR #57628 promoted `Azure.ResourceManager.ComputeLimit` from `1.0.0-beta.1` to `1.0.0` GA, adding two new resource families:

- **`ComputeLimitVmFamilyResource` / `ComputeLimitVmFamilyCollection` / `ComputeLimitVmFamilyData`** — new resource type for managing VM family resources under a subscription location
- **`ComputeLimitFeatureResource` / `ComputeLimitFeatureCollection` / `ComputeLimitFeatureData`** — new resource type with a `Disable` operation for managing compute limit features

The package enables subscriptions to share compute quota limits with guest subscriptions.

## Gaps Found

- The README **Examples** section contains only a generic pointer to `(aka.ms/redacted) with no package-specific code samples
- There is **no `tests/Samples/` directory** — no snippet-backed test files exist for any resource in this package
- The new `ComputeLimitVmFamilyResource` and `ComputeLimitFeatureResource` resources (added in 1.0.0) have **no usage examples** anywhere
- The `Disable` operation on `ComputeLimitFeatureResource` is not demonstrated
- The **Key Concepts** section is entirely generic — it describes no service-specific concepts (e.g., what a &#34;guest subscription&#34;, &#34;shared limit&#34;, &#34;VM family&#34;, or &#34;feature&#34; means in this context)
- The service description in the README header is a single sentence and does not describe the new resource hierarchy


<strong>📐 Implementation Guide</strong>

This section contains step-by-step instructions for a coding agent to implement the changes described above.

### Step 1: Modify files

**File 1:** `sdk/computelimit/Azure.ResourceManager.ComputeLimit/README.md` — **edit**

Replace the `## Key concepts` and `## Examples` sections with service-specific content:

```markdown
## Key concepts

`Azure.ResourceManager.ComputeLimit` enables subscriptions (called *host* subscriptions) to share their allocated Azure compute quota with other subscriptions (*guest* subscriptions). Core resource types:

- **`ComputeLimitGuestSubscriptionResource`** — represents a guest subscription that has been granted access to the host&#39;s compute quota.
- **`ComputeLimitSharedLimitResource`** — represents a shared quota limit configuration between a host and its guests.
- **`ComputeLimitFeatureResource`** — represents an optional compute limit feature that can be enabled or disabled on a subscription.
- **`ComputeLimitVmFamilyResource`** — represents a VM family entry (e.g., `standardDSv3Family`) within a subscription-location scope, used to track or adjust per-family limits.

### Thread safety

All client instance methods are thread-safe. All resource objects are immutable; operations return new instances.

### Additional concepts

[Client options](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/blob/main/sdk/core/Azure.Core/README.md#configuring-service-clients-using-clientoptions) |
[Accessing the response](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/blob/main/sdk/core/Azure.Core/README.md#accessing-http-response-details-using-responset) |
[Long-running operations](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/blob/main/sdk/core/Azure.Core/README.md#consuming-long-running-operations-using-operationt) |
[Handling failures](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/blob/main/sdk/core/Azure.Core/README.md#reporting-errors-requestfailedexception) |
[Diagnostics](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/blob/main/sdk/core/Azure.Core/README.md#logging) |
[Mocking](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/blob/main/sdk/core/Azure.Core/README.md#mocking) |
[Client lifetime]((devblogs.microsoft.com/redacted)

